# Halopress securely creates NUXT_AUTH_SECRET during the first deployment and
# preserves the Cloudflare Worker secret on later deployments.
# To provide your own value for a terminal deployment, uncomment this line and
# pass this file with --secrets-file. It must be at least 24 UTF-8 bytes; use 32
# random bytes (`openssl rand -hex 32`). Never commit the uncommented value.
# NUXT_AUTH_SECRET=replace-with-a-strong-random-value
